# contents of ~/myUtilities/joetoo-base/joetoo-platform-meta/tools --

# assemble-make-conf - builds make.conf for one board, based on one config

# parallel-assemble-make-conf-all -
# use GNU parallel to speed up assembly (safe because each job writes only one unique file)

# assemble-make-conf-all - 
#   calls assemble-make-conf for ENV in crossbuild chroot | for SYSTEM in headless desktop | for every board 

# assemble-make-conf-all-for-board - 
#   calls assemble-make-conf for ENV in crossbuild chroot | for SYSTEM in headless desktop | for **one** board 

# assemble-make-conf-configs <-- this directory holds the config versions
#  assemble-make-conf.desktop.chroot.conf
#  assemble-make-conf.headless.crossbuild.conf
#  assemble-make-conf.desktop.crossbuild.conf
#  assemble-make-conf.interactive.nooverwrite.conf
#  assemble-make-conf.headless.chroot.conf

# make-conf-parts <--- this directory holds the fragments of make.conf to be assembled
